    "what_description": "Polygala heterorhyncha is a species of flowering plant in the family Polygalaceae, native to Africa. It is an annual herb with a woody base, growing up to 30 cm in height, and has a branching habit with numerous leafy stems and axillary leaf clusters. The leaves are alternate, simple, and elliptical in shape, measuring 2-6 cm long and 1-3 cm wide. The flowers are small, pale yellow in color, and arranged in axillary and terminal spikes, each with 5-7 flowers. The fruit is a dehiscent capsule containing 2-3 seeds, 1-2 mm in length.",
