    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Polygala heterorhyncha are flavonoids, such as kaempferol, quercetin, and isorhapontigenin, which have been shown to exhibit anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. The plant also contains iridoids, including polygalasaponin A, which has been found to possess immunomodulatory and anti-inflammatory activities. Additionally, the presence of phenolic acids, including caffeic acid and ferulic acid, contributes to the plant's antioxidant and antimicrobial properties. The iridoid glycosides, including heterorhynchogenin and heterorhynchogenin-3-O-\u03b2-D-galactoside, have been reported to exhibit anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive activities. The combination of these constituents may contribute to the plant's traditional use in treating various health conditions, including inflammation and immunological disorders.",
