    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Polygala heterorhyncha are polygala tea, polygala infusion, dried root tincture, polygala tincture, and polygala decoction. Polygala tea is prepared by steeping the dried root or leaves in boiling water, while polygala infusion is made by steeping the plant material in cold water for an extended period. Dried root tincture is produced through the solvent extraction of the dried root, typically using ethanol or glycerin, whereas polygala tincture is made by macerating the fresh or dried root in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin. Polygala decoction is prepared by boiling the plant material in water, often used for its diuretic and anti-inflammatory properties. These preparations are utilized due to the plant's purported ability to treat various health conditions, such as respiratory issues, fever, and gastrointestinal problems.",
